---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="How Much Does a Website Cost in New Zealand? (2026 Guide) — SiteGenius" description="A comprehensive breakdown of website costs in NZ for 2026. Compare DIY builders, freelancers, agencies, and subscription models. Find the best option for your budget.">
  <article class="pt-32 pb-24">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-4xl">
      <!-- Article Header -->
      <header class="mb-16 text-center">
        <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-sm mb-4 block">Pricing Guide</span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-8 leading-tight">
          How Much Does a Website Cost in <span class="gradient-text">New Zealand?</span> (2026 Guide)
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-muted-200">
          A no-nonsense breakdown of every option — from free DIY builders to premium agencies — so you can make the right call for your business.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Hero Image -->
      <div class="mb-16 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-white/[0.06]">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1554224155-6726b3ff858f?w=1200&h=600&fit=crop" alt="Calculator and laptop showing website cost planning" class="w-full h-64 md:h-80 object-cover" loading="lazy" />
      </div>

      <!-- Article Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert max-w-none">
        <div class="glass p-8 mb-12 rounded-3xl border-neon-cyan/20">
          <p class="text-lg font-medium text-space-800 leading-relaxed m-0 text-muted-100">
            If you've Googled "how much does a website cost in NZ," you've probably seen answers ranging from $0 to $50,000+. The truth is, the right answer depends entirely on what your business actually needs. In this guide we break down every option available to New Zealand businesses in 2026, including real dollar figures in NZD (plus GST), so you can budget with confidence.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">The Four Main Options for NZ Businesses</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          There's no single "right" way to build a website. Each approach comes with trade-offs between cost, quality, flexibility, and ongoing maintenance. Let's look at the four most common paths Kiwi businesses take in 2026.
        </p>

        <!-- Comparison Cards -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 my-10 not-prose">
          <div class="glass-hover p-6 rounded-2xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neon-cyan mb-3">DIY Website Builders</h3>
            <p class="text-2xl font-black text-muted-100 mb-2">$20 – $50/mo</p>
            <p class="text-muted-200 text-sm mb-3">Wix, Squarespace, Shopify (basic)</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-200 text-sm">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> Cheapest upfront cost</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> Easy to get started</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">−</span> Generic templates</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">−</span> Limited SEO control</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">−</span> Slow page speeds</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">−</span> You do all the work</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="glass-hover p-6 rounded-2xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neon-purple mb-3">Freelance Developer</h3>
            <p class="text-2xl font-black text-muted-100 mb-2">$500 – $3,000</p>
            <p class="text-muted-200 text-sm mb-3">One-time project fee</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-200 text-sm">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> More customisation</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> Personal communication</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">−</span> Quality varies wildly</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">−</span> No ongoing support</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">−</span> Updates cost extra</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">−</span> Freelancer may disappear</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="glass-hover p-6 rounded-2xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-500 mb-3">Digital Agency</h3>
            <p class="text-2xl font-black text-muted-100 mb-2">$5,000 – $15,000+</p>
            <p class="text-muted-200 text-sm mb-3">One-time build + retainer</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-200 text-sm">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> High quality output</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> Full strategy & branding</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> Ongoing support available</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">−</span> Expensive upfront</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">−</span> Monthly retainers add up</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">−</span> Overkill for small businesses</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="glass-hover p-6 rounded-2xl border border-neon-cyan/30">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-emerald-500 mb-3">Subscription Model (SiteGenius)</h3>
            <p class="text-2xl font-black text-muted-100 mb-2">$79 – $249/mo</p>
            <p class="text-muted-200 text-sm mb-3">All-inclusive, no upfront cost</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-200 text-sm">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> Professional custom design</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> Hosting, SSL & updates included</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> No big upfront payment</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> Ongoing support & changes</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> Cancel anytime</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold">+</span> SEO optimised from day one</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">Hidden Costs Most People Forget</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          The sticker price of a website is only part of the story. Here are the extras that quietly inflate your total spend — many of which are included in a subscription model like <a href="/pricing" class="text-neon-cyan hover:underline">SiteGenius plans</a>.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-4 mb-8 text-muted-200">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Domain Name:</strong> A .co.nz domain runs about $25–$40/year through registrars like Crazy Domains or 1st Domains. If you want a .com as well, add another $20–$30/year.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Hosting:</strong> NZ-based hosting (important for speed and local SEO) costs $10–$50/month. Cheap overseas hosting can mean slow load times for your Kiwi customers.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>SSL Certificate:</strong> Essential for security and Google rankings. Free with most hosts these days, but some charge $50–$200/year.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Email Setup:</strong> Business email (you@yourdomain.co.nz) through Google Workspace or Microsoft 365 costs $8–$18/user/month.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Ongoing Maintenance:</strong> Security updates, plugin patches, content changes. Budget $50–$150/month if you're not doing it yourself.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>GST:</strong> Don't forget to add 15% GST on top of all these prices. All prices from NZ-based providers will be plus GST unless stated otherwise.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">What You Actually Get at Each Price Point</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Let's be real about what each budget gets you. A $500 website and a $10,000 website are completely different products.
        </p>

        <div class="glass p-8 mb-8 rounded-3xl border-neon-cyan/20">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-muted-100 mb-4">Under $1,000 (DIY or Budget Freelancer)</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-200 mb-2">You'll get a basic template-based site with 3–5 pages. Stock images, limited customisation, and you're largely on your own for SEO and performance. Fine for a side hustle or a basic online presence, but it won't actively bring in customers.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass p-8 mb-8 rounded-3xl border-neon-cyan/20">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-muted-100 mb-4">$1,000 – $5,000 (Mid-Range Freelancer)</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-200 mb-2">Custom WordPress or basic custom-coded site. You'll get a proper design, mobile responsiveness, basic SEO setup, and maybe a contact form with some integrations. Good for small businesses ready to invest, but ongoing maintenance and updates are usually extra.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass p-8 mb-8 rounded-3xl border-neon-cyan/20">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-muted-100 mb-4">$5,000 – $15,000+ (Agency)</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-200 mb-2">Full branding, UX research, custom design, SEO strategy, copywriting, analytics setup, and possibly e-commerce integration. The premium option with premium results — but it's a big cash outlay, especially for a new business.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass p-8 mb-8 rounded-3xl border border-neon-cyan/30">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-muted-100 mb-4">$79 – $249/mo (Subscription Model)</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-200 mb-2">Agency-level quality without the massive upfront cost. You get custom design, fast hosting, SSL, SEO, ongoing updates, and support — all bundled into one predictable monthly payment. No surprises, no hidden fees. Check out our <a href="/pricing" class="text-neon-cyan hover:underline">pricing plans</a> to see what's included.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">Total Cost of Ownership: Year One vs Year Three</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          When comparing options, look at the total cost over time — not just the initial price tag. Here's how the numbers stack up for a typical NZ small business.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-4 mb-8 text-muted-200">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>DIY Builder (Year 1):</strong> $40/mo plan + $35 domain + premium plugins = roughly $600–$800/year. After 3 years: $1,800–$2,400 — and you've spent hundreds of hours on it yourself.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Freelancer (Year 1):</strong> $2,000 build + $300 hosting + $100 maintenance = $2,400. After 3 years: $3,200+ — assuming nothing breaks or needs a rebuild.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Agency (Year 1):</strong> $8,000 build + $600 hosting + $1,200 retainer = $9,800. After 3 years: $13,400+ — serious money.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>SiteGenius Subscription (Year 1):</strong> $149/mo x 12 = $1,788. After 3 years: $5,364 — with continuous updates, support, and hosting included the entire time. Learn more about <a href="/services" class="text-neon-cyan hover:underline">what's included in our service</a>.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">NZ-Specific Considerations</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Building a website in New Zealand comes with some unique factors worth considering.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-4 mb-8 text-muted-200">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>.co.nz Domain:</strong> A .co.nz domain signals to both Google and your customers that you're a legitimate Kiwi business. It's worth the small annual fee for the trust factor alone.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Local Hosting Matters:</strong> Hosting your site in or near NZ (Australia is fine too) ensures fast load times for local visitors. A server in the US adds 200–300ms of latency — enough to hurt your bounce rate.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>GST Implications:</strong> All NZ-based web services charge 15% GST on top. If you're GST-registered, you can claim this back. Factor it into your budget either way.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Privacy Act Compliance:</strong> Your website needs to comply with New Zealand's Privacy Act 2020. This affects how you collect and handle customer data through forms and analytics.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">So, What Should You Spend?</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Our honest recommendation? Don't think of your website as a cost — think of it as your most important employee. It works 24/7, never calls in sick, and talks to every single potential customer before you do.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          For most NZ small businesses, a subscription model offers the best balance of quality, affordability, and peace of mind. You get a professionally built, fast, SEO-optimised website without the scary upfront invoice — and you're never stuck with an outdated site because updates are included.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-10">
          If you want to compare plans side-by-side, head over to our <a href="/pricing" class="text-neon-cyan hover:underline">pricing page</a> — or if you'd rather just have a chat about what your business needs, we're always happy to help.
        </p>

        <!-- CTA Inside Blog -->
        <div class="mt-16 p-10 bg-gradient-to-r from-neon-cyan/10 to-neon-purple/10 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 text-center text-space-900">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-black mb-4 text-muted-100">Get a Professional Website From $79/mo</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-muted-200 mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">No upfront costs, no hidden fees. Just a stunning, fast website that works for your business — with hosting, SSL, and support included.</p>
          <a href="/get-a-quote" class="btn-primary">Get Your Free Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
